Title: Requires the office for the aging to make an annual report on the budget expenditures on behalf of the senior population of the state
Summary: Requires the office for the aging to make an annual report on the budget expenditures on behalf of the senior population of the state every April first.
ActClause: AN ACT to amend the elder law, in relation to requiring the office for the aging to make an annual report on the budget expenditures on behalf of the senior population of the state
